definition.value: This is an AE which is urine which contains white blood cells while appearing sterile by standard culturing techniques.
This is an AE which analysis by HPLC gave a positive predictive value of 81% for Cushing's syndrome.
This is an AE which is bacteriuria without accompanying symptoms of a urinary tract infection.

This is an AE which is a chemical intermediate in the synthesis of artificial vanilla flavorings and is an end-stage metabolite  of the catecholamines (dopamine, epinephrine, and norepinephrine) and it appears on the  urine .
This is an AE which is a condition in which the oxygen transport protein hemoglobin is found in abnormally high concentrations in the urine.
This is an AE which is defined as the presence of blood or red blood cells in the urine.
This is an AE which is a form of urinary incontinence.
This is an AE which is associated urinary tract infections (UTIs).
This is an AE which consists 10% of the total renal biopsy of glomerulonephritis.
This is an AE which occurs with unilateral renal agenesis (URA) in 1/2000 live births - or after uninephrectomy for tumor, trauma, uncontrolled infections or hypertension and post-kidney donation.
This is an AE which is a major complication of kidney transplantation. Many centers respond to PVAN by reducing immunosuppression.
This is an AE which is kidney damage (nephropathy) due to urine flowing backward (reflux) from the bladder toward the kidneys; the latter is called vesicoureteral reflux (VUR).

This is an AE which is a secondary condition in which the adrenal glands do not produce adequate amounts of steroid hormones, primarily cortisol; but may also include impaired production of aldosterone (a mineralocorticoid), which regulates sodium conservation, potassium secretion, and water retention.
This is an AE which is a disorder of the small blood vessels of the kidney.
This is an AE which is a group of clinically similar illnesses caused by the Puumala virus.
This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in the  kidney tissue.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which the kidneys are functioning at less than 15% of normal levels.
This is an AE which is hallmarks of the uremic phenotype and contribute to impaired health status, reduced quality of life, and premature mortality in chronic kidney disease (CKD).
